3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with identifying underlying models in a set of data points, which is a common problem in AI. 
4. cs.GR (Graphics) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with geometric model fitting, which is a common problem in computer graphics. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible sub-category as the paper proposes a greedy algorithm coupled with a data sub-sampling strategy for generating samples.
